4 SJR___ COMMENDING HONDA ON 25 YEARS OF OPERATING ITS
5 AUTOMOTIVE PLANT IN LINCOLN, ALABAMA.
6
7 WHEREAS, Honda operates its Alabama Auto Plant in
8 Lincoln, Alabama, which began manufacturing vehicles in 2001
9 and has grown into one of Alabama's most important
10 automotive manufacturing facilities; and
11 WHEREAS, this facility represents a $3.2 billion
12 capital investment in the state and directly employs more
13 than 4,500 associates, supporting thousands of Alabama
14 families in developing careers in skilled manufacturing,
15 engineering, and technology; and
16 WHEREAS, Honda's economic impact on the State of
17 Alabama also includes 22 authorized dealerships that employ
18 an additional 1,300 Alabama residents and an annually spends
19 $2 billion in parts and materials from Alabama suppliers;
20 and
21 WHEREAS, Honda's Alabama Auto Plant has the annual
22 production capacity to manufacture more than 340,000
23 vehicles and V6 engines each year; and
24 WHEREAS, the Alabama Auto Plant currently produces
25 four Honda models, including the Honda Odyssey, Honda Pilot,
26 Honda Passport, and Honda Ridgeline, which were ranked in
27 the Top 20 of the Cars.com 2025 American-Made Index; and
28 WHEREAS, Honda and its Alabama associates have
Page 1

WHEREAS, Honda and its Alabama associates have
SJR69 Enrolled
29 demonstrated a strong commitment to community service and
30 civic responsibility through volunteerism and charitable
31 giving contributions; now therefore,
32 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
33 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That we do hereby commend Honda
34 on the occasion of its Alabama Auto Plant's 25th Anniversary
35 and recognize Honda's continued investment, production
36 excellence, and commitment to Alabama.
37 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, That we extend our sincere
38 appreciation to Honda's associates, leadership, and partners
39 for their role in strengthening Alabama's manufacturing
40 economy and for helping build a legacy of innovation and
41 opportunity over the past 25 years.
